<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-12T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-12T07:00:00-05:00" n="181" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2056: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-12T20:00:00+08:00">October 12, 1931—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 12—9:47 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>748. Your 388, October 11, 6 p.m. Since Hanson and Salisbury probably are
                            en route to Taonan, Colonel Margetts is being sent to Chinchow tonight,
                            while Lieutenant Brown will join him there from Mukden.</p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>